@startuml fig-A02-demo-scenario
skinparam backgroundColor white
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center

title IDS — E3 Demo Scenario (Benign vs Malicious Contrast)

participant "Examiner" as EX #FFE0B2
participant "scripts/" as SH #ECEFF1
participant "h1\n(attacker)" as ATK #FFCDD2
participant "h2\n(victim)" as VIC #C8E6C9
participant "IDS" as IDS #E1BEE7

== STEP 1 — BENIGN TRAFFIC (no alert expected) ==

EX -> SH : ./run_benign.sh
SH -> ATK : curl h2:80 (single HTTP request)
ATK -> VIC : GET /index.html
VIC --> ATK : HTTP 200 OK
IDS -> IDS : evaluate: no threshold\nbreached, no pattern match
note right of IDS #E8F5E9 : zero alerts — negative case validated

== STEP 2 — SCAN ATTACK ==

EX -> SH : ./run_scan.sh
SH -> ATK : TCP connect to ports 1–100
ATK -[#E53935]> VIC : SYN to 100 ports (5 s window)
IDS -> IDS : threshold exceeded (>=N ports)
IDS -[#E53935]> IDS : SCAN alert emitted
note right of IDS #FFCDD2 : alert log: source, ports, severity

== STEP 3 — PAYLOAD ATTACK ==

EX -> SH : ./run_payload.sh
SH -> ATK : crafted HTTP request with SQL marker
ATK -[#E53935]> VIC : GET /?q=DROP TABLE
IDS -> IDS : substring match on payload
IDS -[#E53935]> IDS : PAYLOAD alert emitted
note right of IDS #FFCDD2 : alert log: rule, matched pattern

== STEP 4 — EVIDENCE REVIEW ==

EX -> SH : ./collect_evidence.sh
SH -> SH : save PCAP + alerts.jsonl\n+ summary.md under artifacts/
EX -> EX : verify traceability:\nalert → rule → packets

legend right
  E3 validates: at least two distinct alerts,
  one negative case (no false positives)
  and full traceability from rule to PCAP.
  Mini security audit covers input validation.
endlegend
@enduml
